c:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mb-6 not-prose","children":["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2.5 border-l-4 border-yellow-400/50 pl-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Novartis acquires Pikavation for up to $3B"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Lead drug SNV4818 in early trials for HR+/HER2- breast cancer"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"No proof yet it outperforms existing PI3Kα therapies"}]]}]]}]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["Novartis’ $3 billion acquisition of ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.genengnews.com/topics/oncology/novartis-acquires-pikavation-for-up-to-3b-expanding-cancer-pipeline/","children":"Pikavation"}]," isn’t just another pipeline expansion. It’s a calculated bet on ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"SNV4818"}],", a pan-mutant selective PI3Kα inhibitor now in early-stage trials for ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.cancer.gov/types/breast","children":"HR+/HER2- metastatic breast cancer"}],"—a space where existing PI3K inhibitors like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.fda.gov/drugs/resources-information-approved-drugs/piqray-alpelisib","children":"alpelisib"}]," already struggle with toxicity and modest efficacy."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The move signals Novartis’ confidence in overcoming a key limitation of current PI3Kα drugs: their narrow mutant selectivity. SNV4818’s ",["$","em",null,{"children":"pan-mutant"}]," design aims to cover a broader range of PIK3CA mutations, which occur in ~40% of HR+/HER2- breast cancers. But here’s the catch: ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"this is still Phase 1"}],". The only public data come from a ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://ascopubs.org/doi/abs/10.1200/JCO.2023.41.16_suppl.1012","children":"small, non-randomized dose-escalation study"}]," (n < 50), with no head-to-head comparisons against standard therapies like CDK4/6 inhibitors or fulvestrant."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["What we know: SNV4818 shows ",["$","em",null,{"children":"preliminary"}]," tumor shrinkage in some patients, with a safety profile Novartis calls \"manageable.\" What we don’t: whether it will outperform ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa1713584","children":"taselisib"}],", the PI3Kα inhibitor that failed to win FDA approval due to lackluster survival benefits. The acquisition price suggests optimism—but in oncology, Phase 1 promise rarely survives Phase 3 scrutiny."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/novartis-bets-3b-on-a-pi3k-inhibitorbut-how-solid-/subtitle.jpg","alt":"A high-stakes gamble on a pan-mutant inhibitor—with Phase 1 data as the only hand shown so far.","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"A high-stakes gamble on a pan-mutant inhibitor—with Phase 1 data as the only hand shown so far."}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The regulatory path for SNV4818 is unclear. PI3K inhibitors have a ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41573-020-0073-9","children":"checkered history"}],": alpelisib gained approval in 2019 but carries a ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.fda.gov/media/128937/download","children":"black-box warning"}]," for severe hyperglycemia, while others like buparlisib were abandoned due to toxicity. Novartis’ gamble hinges on two unproven assumptions: that pan-mutant selectivity translates to better efficacy, and that SNV4818’s side effects will be tolerable enough to justify its use alongside endocrine therapies."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["For patients today, ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"nothing changes"}],". SNV4818 remains years away from potential approval, and current HR+/HER2- treatment guidelines still prioritize ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://ascopubs.org/doi/full/10.1200/JCO.21.02540","children":"CDK4/6 inhibitors"}]," like palbociclib. The real test will come in later-stage trials: Can SNV4818 demonstrate ","$L15"," responses, or will it join the list of PI3K drugs that show early activity but fail to move the survival needle?"]}],"\n","$L16","\n","$L17"]}]
