16:["$","p",null,{"children":["The acquisition also raises questions about Novartis’ strategy. With ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa2032240","children":"KRAS inhibitors"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.fda.gov/drugs/resources-information-approved-drugs/enhertu-fam-trastuzumab-deruxtecan-nxki","children":"ADCs"}]," dominating recent oncology deals, is doubling down on PI3Kα—a pathway with repeated clinical disappointments—a bold move or a costly distraction?"]}]
17:["$","p",null,{"children":"If successful, pan-mutant PI3Kα inhibitors could reshape HR+/HER2- treatment. But the bar is high: patients need more than incremental progress. The next milestone? Phase 2 data proving SNV4818 isn’t just another me-too PI3K failure."}]
